{"word":"ἔρως","slug":"ἔρως","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔρως</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔραμαι'><el>ἔραμαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>love</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>:— <i>love of</i> a thing, <i>desire for</i> it, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>loves, amours</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; in <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, of <i>passionate joy</i>, <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>φρίσσω</el> II. 3.<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as prop. n. <i>the god of love, Eros, Amor</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}